  "name": "Beam Break Alarm",
  "lesson": {
    "title": "Beam Break Alarm",
    "description": "Same optical interrupt wiring as lesson 72: USB → 150Ω → L+ / L- lights the slot; USB → T → 10kΩ → junction → S+ / S- → ground reads the beam. When the beam is blocked the tap voltage rises, the NMOS turns on, and the drain branch drives a buzzer (USB → T → 150Ω → buzzer → drain) instead of a red LED. Quiet with a clear beam; block the slot to sound the alarm. On a real plate the buzzer can couple into the sensor — a quick block and release is clearer than holding the beam broken. Compare lesson 66, lesson 70, and lesson 72. Opto at 0°; NMOS at 90°; buzzer at 90°."
  },
